caption: Ordered shrimp and there were 4 small soggy shrimp, most likely bag shrimp for $12, Gross.  Ordered the cheese tray too.  Ate 2 bites.  Entrees were worth 1/2 of what they are charging. I don't like writing bad reviews,but it was that bad.
Terrible. Food was awful...we were the only ones in the restaurant. Go somewhere else

Honestly shocking how bad a restaurant in a Westin could possibly be. Only reason I give it 1 star is because the bartender was friendly. It was not her fault the food was atrocious. I ordered tomato bisque soup and a steak sandwich. The soup was the consistency of jello and actually jiggled. The steak sandwich was basically a piece of jerky on a roll. There had to have been a cup of salt used on the sandwich and fries. Fries were undercooked and awful. Even the soda was flat.
The restaurant was beautiful, service outstanding and atmosphere perfect.
Don’t bother. Bad food. Over priced. Not at all near Schula’s quality. Plus the environment was a bit long in the tooth and worn.

Would appear to be a nice atmosphere. Tried to eat at this establishment A couple of times during a recent stay. One time they said it was to late at night to order food which is understandable (although all those around us were eating). We were told to go back to our rooms and order room service? Second attempt was a breakfast, could not get seated. Waited and waited no luck. Establishment was almost empty but told no open tables for a few more minutes. Ended up leaving.
Awesome service! Nice view!
The food was delicious
Great restaurant when you don't want to leave the hotel

Food was delicious each time I ate there (3×) but the breakfast and dinner service was really slow (esp dinner), but our lunch server, Sidone, was really awesome and attentive! My fave server by far! And she gave us great food recommendations! For breakfast I ordered the French toast, lunch I had the Prime Burger (and added a fried egg) with steak fries and dinner I had the half honey glazed salmon with the beets salad. I would highly recommend all those dishes!
The food is very tasty
Limited menu for lunch but food is pretty good.  However, I suggest you forego the grilled fish sandwich - fish had very little flavor. Boring.

It has been a long time since we have been eating somewhere and in the middle of the meal actually have a conversation about how we can't wait to give them a great review later. We were staying at the Westin for a horror movie convention. Nourish catered to the convention by giving us a discount on our meal and providing a specialized horror movie themed menu. But that was not all. Every single person that worked there greeted us with warm welcomes and a smile. Since it was just us they made sure to sit us where we would have some privacy and a wonderful view of the city. To top it off our server Walter was fantastic, our drinks were made very well and the food was impressive. So much that we went back the 2nd day to eat there again. Highly recommend giving them a try if you are staying at the Westin of visting the convention center (connected via the sky way)

In a word, "yum". I ordered the half turkey club which was served with cole slaw and sweet potato fries. The only sweet potato I have ever had interest in is pie, until now. I don't know if there is a special seasoning they use for the fries or what. All I know is that I love 'em, I love 'em; I want more of 'em. This little "happy" meal is adequately proportioned and adequately priced.  While all of the staff were attentive and friendly, Samantha at the bar and Lori are the employees that stood out most.  If you are looking for a new experience, take a closer look at Nourish inside the Westin Hotel on Washington Street in Indianapolis. You will not be disappointed. Bon Appetite!
Was seated. Waited 15 minutes, watched people that were sat after us place their order. Decided to leave as we did not have all night.
It is a delightfully delicious place to eat. It is always very busy and a little cramped but it is definitely worth it.

This is the new name of the previous Shula's restaurant at Westin Indianapolis. The decor is exactly what it was for the previous restaurant and does not remotely convey what one would expect for a contemporary restaurant. The service was lacking and we had to wait multiple times for the server to return to the table. It would have been expected if it were busy, but there were only two other tables that had customers at the time and each had their own server. There were only three of us, but rather than put us at a booth or 4 top, were were placed at two separate 2 tops, which made conversing and sharing the appetizers quite difficult. The food was nothing I'd ever want to order again. I had gotten a burger that was ordered medium rare, and it came rare to rare/blue and was a complete salt bomb. There was not enough water on the table to take away the burn caused by the overpowering salt content. The steak fries accompanying the burger were just the opposite in seasoning, but were the same in the fact they were quite undercooked. The egg that was added to the burger was also well overcooked. The other dishes ordered at the table were just as poor from what was described from the ones who ordered them.
We ate lunch here and for breakfast the next morning we had the buffet. Everything was delicious and the staff was helpful and friendly.
Great food and staff
Staff was great but breakfast buffet was low quality, fake eggs, stale pasties, $16
Went for breakfast and FROZE. Definitely wouldn't go back for breakfast. It must have been 50 degrees. Tried them out for lunch and had a good experience. The prime burger was DELICIOUS!
I had got the hamburger well done it were burnt and hard
Dropped in for the tasty breakfast buffet while in for a convention at the Westin hotel. Great food, great service, no complaints here. Fantastic job!

Don’t do it. Maybe 30 people inside the actual restaurant and we waited almost two hours for our food. All we were told was that they were extremely busy with parties downstairs and they were doing their best. Not acceptable.  I couldn’t tell you how the food is because I still have not received it. Update to the review, the food was great when I did receive it. Changed to 3 stars. Management did comp the meal for the inconvenience.

Food was really well executed, possibly _under priced_. I had the grilled chicken sandwich which was juicy and well dressed. Steak fries were great. My girlfriend was really happy with the beet salad and margherita flat bread.

Nourish was so tasteful. The staff, Excellent. The food, amazing. And so nicely located in the hotel and convention center, I highly recommend.

Just OK at breakfast. Runny eggs on the buffet, but the omlet off the menu was good.

Beautiful dining. I’m simple, i had the baked chicken breast, crab macaroni, and spinach. Fresh bread and lobster bisque was great as well. Ron the waiter was excellent. And to end a great birthday dinner. A slice of chocolate cake to share with good friends.

Service poor. Steak tough. Didn’t have all entrees offered on menu.  Drinks had to be remade.  Even had to ask for water. Never offered second drink. All in all very disappointing from what used to be a favorite restaurant for special occasions.
Always love shulas steak house. Some things have changed since I have been there last.  Highly recommend this place. However, it is not as good as it used to be 2 years ago! Still excellent though!
Great for lunch and dinner. Every time we've visited we leave over pleased. The filet is amazing and the bread is so good you'll want 32 baskets of it. Great wine selection, too.
Getting tired
Garbage service. Went for breakfast, and they plain face told me that they had no tables available when the place was visibly empty. Apparently they didn’t want money 🤷‍♂️
Fantastic!
Best steakhouse in INDY
Incredible food and service
Very nice and friendly, and very clean. If you ever want to get away from home and away from kids this is the place to go. Kids are welcome as well though.
Delicious food and great service! Syd was extremely pleasant and an exceptional server!
Perfect environment. Excellent food!
The service was top notch my server Lori was excellent and food was awesome great place to eat definitely going back again

Service? Started out very poorly, the door guy seemed lost and spoke little english, we decided to sit in the bar (it was lunch) and waited an extremely long time for lunch. Food? It was excellent, the burger was one of the best Ive ever had, it was lean but very tender. Salad wedge had generous portions of real blue cheese, and the calamari was cooked with a crisp crunchy outer layer while juicy inside.  When it came time for the bill the manager said “don’t worry we got it” due to it taking so long, I never expect fast service when I go to a nicer restaurant in fact I prefer to wait longer so the fact they didn’t charge me was extremely classy.

if i could give this a zero i would, but the busboy we had pretty much was the reason we were able to finish our meal. The busboy was amazing and attentive, but besides the bread they give their customers, this restaurants lacks in food, service and management, maybe it is b/c I am from New York and we have higher standards but i literally spent 5-10 minutes talking to the waiter, ensuring that my meal had no bacon in it. When my food came out it had bacon. Not only did he take my order wrong but it took forever to get our check and when we confronted him about our order being wrong he had no response. We literally had to tell the busboy we wanted our check to get the attention of the waiter, bc the waiter barely stopped by our table, another reason we waited to the end to tell him about the food order being wrong. He got his manager and this guy was an useless as the waiter. Horrible service and a horrible experience. Please read this review and eat somewhere else.
I had the breakfast buffet and it was ok.  Overcooked but lack of other options in the area.

OMG!! Absolutely wonderful food! I will be back the next time I visit Indy.

The food for the party was overcooked on at least two of the steaks. Totally not the same experience as what I had at the Orlando one.
Way over priced. Better steak at 5 other steakhouses within four blocks.

This place sucks. I've been waiting to go there for over 2 years and finally took my wife and daughter. My 22oz rib eye was over cooked so I had them to take it back and it returned back RARE. my daughter's filet was well done verses medium. The brussel sprouts were over cooked. Felt sorry the waitress because she knew the food wasn't cooked right . The waiter couldn't answer any questions about the menu. Finally the manager came out but didn't even apologize.  To his credit , he did take care of the bill which he should have. Probably won't be back unless it's under someone else TAB!

This is in the Wyndham hotel we stayed at.  Pricey, but we expected that.  We chose to split a tomato burrata salad, ribeye, and side of creamed spinach.  The steak was overcooked (not what I expected at a steak house) and the meat itself was slightly mealy.  The tomato salad was good but could have used some lettuce or more burrata to cut the acidity of all the vinegar.  The creamed spinach was fantastic. It was pretty late and we were one of two tables there, but the service was so slow and unattentive.  Overall, a fine option but just underwhelming.

OMGosh !!! Talk about a fantastic meal. I ordered the "Surf & Turf". Not only was it exquisite, the lobster was immense and the fillet was huge. There was so much food that we had enough to take home and have two more meals. The restaurant was beautiful, service outstanding and atmosphere perfect. LOVED IT !!!

The steakhouse/lounge is on 2 in the very back by the glass staircase; within the hotel.  We went up for casual drinks and confronted by a company having awards meal and they were very loud. So, we left, shortly following, after drink. Chose not eat there by of the level of loudness.

Been here an hour, waiting on my lunch order. Frustrating.

Don't get me wrong, the steaks and concept are as good as ever. But the vibe needs work. It's kind of like a guy who has ED. In his mind he still wants it, but there's some disconnect that's just confusing and frustrating. He doesn't know if he'll ever even try again...
Horrible service. Waited at front door for about 15 min no one would even come to seat us.  So we left

Our food was great and was as we ordered but the service was slow and lacking. We payed $150.00 for our meal and did not receive the service that we should have for that price. I had the Cowboy Ribeye and it was excellent and cooked perfect. My wife had the chicken and it was delicious as well. I had to use my cell phone light so that I could check to make sure the steak was cook properly because it was so dark. There were only five other groups and only one was bigger then our group of nine so there was no reason for the service was so slow. We have spent less and had the same quality of food and better service from other high end steak houses.
We had cowboy steak and scallops. Nothing was hot, scallops were fishy tasting, steak was okay, but not great. We won't go back !!!!

Let me say I have been to the Shula's in Chicago and the experience there was great. Wish I could say the same for this location, but the service was terrible, no one at host/hostess stand, walked in couldn't get the attention of anyone that worked there, just ignored me as I asked for a table. finally got a hostess and was like pulling teeth to get a table, she was very quick to offer me open seating at the bar area (which was full) as the sit down table area was completely empty compared to the bar area. slow service, when seated and a few rowdy patrons completely ruined the meal which was not great anyways.  Save your money and your time and go to one of the many other better Steak Houses in Indy.
Delicious!!
Good steakhouse given the competition downtown Indy
Filet one on the most divine in my life!  Remarkable cut of meat ... I will return - great service.
Terrible place, very rude personal, slow service and expensive. The food nothing special.

We went there last night 8/26/17.  It was the worst steak I've ever eaten.  When we were in Florida in February we ate at a Shula's in the dolphin hotel at Disney world.  That night was the best steak I ever ate.  Ever!  And I raise beef.  But Indys downtown inside the Westin is terrible!  My wife had the French onion soup and it was amazing.  I got the thick cut bacon as an app and it was very good. But our steak was terrible.  I originally ordered a 48 oz porter house which we were sharing.  We asked for medium well. Then I remembered that when we were in Florida our waiter suggested we get 2-24s inside of the 48 since we wanted it med-well.  So when our server came back to say it would take 45 minutes to cook our steak we said that's fine but we could switch our order to 2 24s she said oh I've already put it in it will be fine.....  Fast forward close to an hour later we get our steak.  They cut each side off the bone.  My wife took the filet part and it wasn't terrible  but no near the quality someone would expect from a $90 steak.  My strip side was terrible.  It was well past well done.  It was basically a roast that had been cooked way to long and with absolutely no seasoning..   Just terrible!! I am not a person who complains about my food. I deal with the public and I understand.  But after sleeping on it.  Never again will I eat at the Indianapolis Shula's!!!

The perfect place for a good meal & incredibly great service regardless if you are going for a business meeting, casually stopping by, or celebrating a bday. The steaks & twice baked potatoes are kickass by far. m/
Amazing food! I had the ribeye and grilled asparagus. Jason was a wonderful server with great recommendations! You may even run into a Colt's player or two 😉

Went for breakfast yesterday morning and my wife who has diabetes asked for sugar free syrup. What they brought to the table had an expiration date of February 2016. The waitress checked and all the bottles they had were dated the same date. We thought maybe they just refill the bottles with fresh syrup but the waitress said they didn't. Went back again this morning and asked for sugar free syrup and was brought the same old bottle.  Sad, especially since we were in town for a diabetes conference.
The service was horrible, and food was eh. Cross this off your bucket list
Slower than hell and only 12 people there. Burger was great, shrimp on the Caesar was terrible.

Walked in and couldnt get seated everyone working was busy playing on their phones and talking. I counted about 5 customers in the whole place. The menu was unbelievable.  40 dollars or more for a steak and then if you wanted a side to go with it that was another 10 dollars.  I ordered a filet cooked medium rare. When it finally came out there was not even the slightest bit of pink in the middle. They reluctantly offered me another one and said they "hoped" it would come out right.  By the time it finally came out my friend was finished with their whole meal. The second steak wasn't right but better and had a sort of undesirable taste.  And my asparagus was cold and raw. Hands down the worst steak I've ever had.  If I could give them 0 stars, I would.  They could have at the very least comped the dessert.
The best steak I have ever had and the bartender Cam was knowledgeable on every drink we ordered.
The food taste good. The presentation was fine and the service was good.
Best Steak In Indianapolis
Breakfast buffett was varied, very well presented and tasty. Coffee was strong and plentiful. Our server Amy took very good care of our large party. Recommended!

The food was good and the servers were nice enough. Service was just very slow. It seemed as if they were not prepared for dinner service. It took a long time to get seated even though there was only one group before us and the restaurant just started dinner service so there were only a few tables filled. Dinner rolles weren't ready and took ages to come out. When you have hungry 2 and 4 year olds, this is very important.
Don't waist your time!

I have eaten at Shula's in South Beach and Chicago, I have to say that I'm not sure if the location in Indianapolis is an impostor or they just lost the recipe book! I will first say that the wait staff was fantastic. My 10yr old was being picky, and our waitress was very accommodating. We ordered a New York Strip with peppercorn sauce, an 8oz Filet, BBQ Shrimp, Crab Mac & Cheese, and creamed spinach. Of all of those items, I would say that the Strip steak was really the only decent thing, with zero help from the peppercorn sauce that resemble/ tasted brown gravy with a few peppercorns thrown in. That said, I can get a New York strip like this at Outback. All of the food was kind of bland. The Mac & Cheese needed salt and pepper, the creamed spinach was not creamy at all, and the bbq shrimp sauce was terrible. Overwhelming the flavor of the shrimp and bacon. If I didn't know there was bacon on the shrimp, I would have been able to tell by taste alone. And my Wife's Filet... I will be the first to admit that I am not a fan of Filet to begin with, but her "medium" filet was more like medium well, and dry, and under seasoned. Since she is a person who will generally not send food back because she feels bad, she got to eat a $43 piece of leather. I would not go back to this location again.

We were here with a bigger party in a private dining room. The service was very nice and friendly, but certainly understaffed and not able to fill up drinks and take care of empty plates in time. The Steaks were an immense disappointment. My 12oz Filet was cold, served on a cold plate and had a weird taste that was not necessarily aged. The béarnaise sauce was cold as well and tasted like from a can. Mushrooms  were simply cut up champignons. Despite of the very friendly service , the food certainly needs to improve for the price paid. Would rather recommend St. Elmo's and other real and honest places without such a blending brand name.
This review is specifically for the restaurant located in Fort Myers airport.  The food was good, but the staff wasn't accommodating.
Food was good but expensive. Staff was very very polite!

When they came to take our order at our table of 6 I asked the server if he should write down our order? He stated he would be fine as he is a professional. When our order came I had the wrong salad, asked for a wedge and received a house salad. I told them no problem because I was really hungry. When my meal came I was not at the table and my steak was well done, I asked for Medium Rare. My friend sitting next to me, her steak was rare and she couldn't eat most of it. We ordered different steaks so we couldn't even trade. I sent my meal back and they brought me the correct one after the rest of my table had already eaten. I ended up eating the rare parts of my friends steak that she didn't want. We've been to Shulas in different cities and this visit was not enjoyable at all. I don't get to eat out often at fancy restaurants so, when I do I expect the service to be better. The food tasted good and the people were very nice. But, if you go here make sure your waiter writes down your order.

Streaks were charred on the outside and bleeding on the inside, not much seasoning, and the sides were bland. I had to send the steak back and have it recooked. Considering the other steakhouses within close proximity I def expected more. However, the waitstaff, and the Hennessy side car cocktail were fantastic!
Best  steak I've had (in the US anyway)

I had always wanted to go to this restaurant and finally had the opportunity in Fort Myer Airport.  Wow! Was I disappointed!  Chris, an older man that waited on me, needs to reevaluate his decision to be in the service industry.  I had to ask for my flatware, a refill, and my bill.  Someone else brought my food and I wasn't extremely excited about the taste of it!  I went ahead and ordered desert as well thinking it would help kill a little more time.  In the end, my bill was $40 and I left $6 for a tip, although I have yet to understand what the tip was actually for.  As he picked up the bill and saw his tip, he was shaking his head as if he could not believe I would have the audacity to ONLY leave 15% instead of 20%!?? REALLY???  People like that deserve no tip at all.

The good: the sides - plentiful and delicious (the creamy spinach was the best I've ever tasted)  The "OK": the steak - the medium came out pretty dark, so if I return I will go with a grade below what I want the value - between 2 $50 steaks, I would not expect both to be improperly cooked, but they were otherwise good  The bad: the service: being painfully short staffed is something I would understand in a tiny family cafe, but not a steak house that will give you a bill this high, and being treated not rudely but as if we were inconveniencing the server was off-putting  Overall, Shula's has good, not great food for a steep price, and there are alternatives within waking distance that are better in every aspect.
Excellent service, great atmosphere, strong selection on the menu and perfectly cooked. Well done Coach.

I ordered steak, I said pink no blood. It came to me tasting like ashes, and it was not pink. the coffee was not hot and the server did not listen to our order. I ate there IN 2012 and it was excellent. WHAT HAPPENED?
Okay
One of the best steaks I've had in Indy
Reset in the bar and ate from the bar menu. It was mid-afternoon and the bartender took care of this. His service was awesome the food was great!
Super Expensive - Mediocre Food - Horrible Customer service
Dined there numerous times during my stay at the westin. Absolutely stellar service and food. Very pricey but certainly worth it if you're looking for a great meal. Treated like royalty as well.

The food was awesome! We ordered the 6oz. Filet with grilled asparagus and green beans. The service was a little slow but the atmosphere of the restaurant and the low music overshadowed that part. Will definitely be back.
Great place!! Service was superb!! Food was excellent!! Can't wait to comeback!!
Steak was done well and the service was excellent. No issues getting a table walking in.

Not a whole lot. It was my birthday and when I arrived I was seated promptly by the hostess. From there the night went downhill. The servers were nowhere to be found most of the time and when the food came the prime rib was tasteless, the baked potatoes were cold and the asparagus was barely steamed and the hollandaise sauce was bland. They had the nerve to only remove the salads which was about $9.00 and then they gave me this little box of chocolate and said "Happy Birthday" never again.
Worst service ever. Put in very back corner and forgotten about. Had to flag down server for everything. Will not be going back.

I went there to celebrate my babys recovery from illness while at the Riley children's hospital.  We were given excellent service; we enjoyed   their filet mignon dinner with a complimentary desert of ice cream over chocolate chip cookie.  Our waiters were students of IUPUI and our bill was under 200.00

Steaks were overcooked and tough; Caesar salad had no flavor; bill for our dinner was outrageous ($200 for the two of us) and the parking fee ($30) was the final shock.  Will never visit this restaurant again.  Will stick with Morton's when wanting a great steak dinner and evening out on the town.
Food was good, staff was pleasant, & the bill was outrageous.

I stayed for one night at Westin Hotel. I got there to  Shula's for a beer and a burger. everything was going great till I'm done with my beer and the waiter came to ask for another one. I asked: do you have a refill. He replied: yeah but you have to pay. his answer was polite. but I was shocked that he went to the hostesses and joked about it loud and they started to laugh. I called him: did you just joked about me. He answered: would you like another beer. I replied: call your manager. The manager came and started apologizing, she was nice and dealt with with the situation very nicely. and offered me to have my meal on the house. I refused the offer and asked for my check. without eating my burger.  I'm sorry Shula's I can't stay in a place where I have to pay to make jokes of me.  I don't know any of the staff's names, but you can check the staff in the shift. I just left from there and right now it's Sept 9 2014, 7:00pm
Worst service I have ever experienced.  We had a rude waiter who we actually heard cursing another customer.

First of all, the ambiance was delightful and we were seated right by a window with a terrific view of downtown Indy.  All of the service staff were friendly, courteous, and helpful.  We were made to feel special with what felt like personal service.  Our filets were perfectly cooked and very tasty.  I highly recommend the roasted corn side dish and the creme brulee trio for dessert.  As we were celebrating my wife's birthday, our service staff wished her a happy day and presented her with a small box of truffles as a "parting gift".  We had a most enjoyable evening and would definitely go back.
The steaks here are better than the ones at St.Elmo's
I ran dry on my drink 3 times and he was in no rush to refill it
